No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Tazobactam is only minimally metabolised and is eliminated renally whereas ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. El tazobactam sólo se metaboliza mínimamente y se elimina principalmente sin cambios por vía renal, mientras que es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Tazobactam is only minimally metabolised and is eliminated renally via glomerular filtration and active renal secretion by OAT1/3. An interaction is unlikely as albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El tazobactam sólo se metaboliza mínimamente y se elimina por vía renal mediante filtración glomerular y secreción renal activa por OAT1/3. Una interacción es poco probable ya que la albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Lenalidomide undergoes limited metabolism and is eliminated renally. Lenalidomide does not induce or inhibit CYPs or UGTs. Although lenalidomide is a weak substrate of P-gp, no effect due to inhibition of P-gp by atazanavir is expected as coadministration with quinidine (a strong P-gp inhibitor) had no significant effect on lenalidomide.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La lenalidomida experimenta un metabolismo limitado y se elimina por vía renal. La lenalidomida no inhibe ni induce los CYP o las UGT. Aunque la lenalidomida es un sustrato débil de P-gp, no se espera ningún efecto debido a la inhibición de P-gp por atazanavir ya que la administración conjunta con quinidina (un inhibidor fuerte de P-gp) no tuvo un efecto significativo sobre la lenalidomida.

Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. Lenalidomide undergoes limited metabolism and is eliminated renally. Lenalidomide does not induce or inhibit CYPs or UGTs. Although lenalidomide is a weak substrate of P-gp, no effect due to inhibition of P-gp by elvitegravir/cobicistat is expected as coadministration with quinidine (a strong P-gp inhibitor) had no significant effect on lenalidomide. No interaction is expected with emtricitabine as lenalidomide does not inhibit renal transporters. However, lenalidomide has been associated with serious nephrotoxicity including proximal and distal tubular damage, glomerular effects and Fanconi syndrome and therefore renal function should be closely monitored when coadministered with tenofovir (derived from tenofovir alafenamide) due to potential renal additive toxicity.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. La lenalidomida experimenta un metabolismo limitado y se elimina por vía renal. La lenalidomida no inhibe ni induce los CYP o las UGT. Aunque la lenalidomida es un sustrato débil de P-gp, no se espera ningún efecto debido a la inhibición de P-gp por elvitegravir/cobicistat ya que la administración conjunta con quinidina (un inhibidor fuerte de P-gp) no tuvo un efecto significativo sobre la lenalidomida. No se espera interacción con emtricitabina ya que la lenalidomida no inhibe los transportadores renales. Además, se ha asociado a la lenalidomida con nefrotoxicidad grave que incluye daño tubular proximal y distal, efectos glomerulares y síndrome de Fanconi y, por lo tanto, la función renal debe controlarse estrechamente cuando se coadministra con tenofovir (derivado de tenofovir alafenamida) debido a la posible toxicidad aditiva renal.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Lenalidomide undergoes limited metabolism and is eliminated renally. Lenalidomide does not induce or inhibit CYPs or UGTs. Although lenalidomide is a weak substrate of P-gp, quinidine (a strong P-gp inhibitor) was shown to have no significant effect on lenalidomide exposure.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La lenalidomida experimenta un metabolismo limitado y se elimina por vía renal. La lenalidomida no inhibe ni induce los CYP o las UGT. Aunque la lenalidomida es un sustrato débil de P-gp, se demostró que la quinidina (un inhibidor fuerte de la P-gp) no tiene un efecto significativo sobre la exposición a la lenalidomida.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Lenalidomide undergoes limited metabolism and is eliminated renally whereas ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. La lenalidomida experimenta metabolismo limitado y se elimina principalmente por vía renal, mientras que es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Lenalidomide undergoes limited metabolism and is eliminated renally. Albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids. In vitro human microsomal studies and limited in vivo drug-drug interaction data indicate that albuvirtide has no inhibiting or inducing properties on P450 enzymes.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La lenalidomida experimenta un metabolismo limitado y se elimina por vía renal. La albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes. Los estudios microsómicos humanos in vitro y los datos limitados de interacción farmacológica in vivo indican que la albuvirtida no tiene propiedades inhibidoras o inductoras en las enzimas P450.

co_drug_trade_names: Herceptin, Herzuma, Kanjinti, Ogivri, Ontruzant, Trazimera
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Trastuzumab is a monoclonal IgG antibody. Elimination is similar to endogenous IgG and occurs primarily via proteolytic catabolism.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El trastuzumab es un anticuerpo monoclonal IgG. La eliminación es similar a la IgG endógena y ocurre principalmente a través del catabolismo proteolítico.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Trastuzumab is a monoclonal IgG antibody. Elimination is similar to endogenous IgG and occurs primarily via proteolytic catabolism.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El trastuzumab es un anticuerpo monoclonal IgG. La eliminación es similar a la IgG endógena y ocurre principalmente a través del catabolismo proteolítico.

Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. Trastuzumab is a monoclonal IgG antibody. Elimination is similar to endogenous IgG and occurs primarily via proteolytic catabolism. No pharmacokinetic interaction is expected with zidovudine, however, due to the risk of additive hematological toxicity, hematological parameters should be monitored if coadministered.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. El trastuzumab es un anticuerpo monoclonal IgG. La eliminación es similar a la IgG endógena y ocurre principalmente a través del catabolismo proteolítico. No se espera interacción farmacocinética con zidovudina. Sin embargo, debido al riesgo de toxicidad hematológica aditiva, los parámetros hematológicos deben monitorearse si se administran conjuntamente.

co_drug_trade_names: Herceptin, Herzuma, Kanjinti, Ogivri, Ontruzant, Trazimera
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Trastuzumab is a monoclonal IgG antibody. Elimination is similar to endogenous IgG and occurs primarily via proteolytic catabolism. An interaction is unlikely as albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El trastuzumab es un anticuerpo monoclonal IgG. La eliminación es similar a la IgG endógena y ocurre principalmente a través del catabolismo proteolítico. Una interacción es poco probable ya que la albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes.

co_drug_trade_names: Herceptin, Herzuma, Kanjinti, Ogivri, Ontruzant, Trazimera
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Trastuzumab is a monoclonal IgG antibody. Elimination is similar to endogenous IgG and occurs primarily via proteolytic catabolism throughout the body.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El trastuzumab es un anticuerpo monoclonal IgG. La eliminación es similar a la IgG endógena y ocurre principalmente a través del catabolismo proteolítico en todo el cuerpo.

Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but is not recommended. Trastuzumab emtansine is a monoclonal antibody-drug conjugate. Trastuzumab does not undergo CYP mediated metabolism, however, DM1 (an active component of emtansine) is metabolized by CYP3A4. Coadministration is not recommended due to the potential for an increase in DM1 exposure and toxicity. Consider switching to an antiretroviral regimen with no inhibitory effects on CYP3A4. If coadministration is unavoidable, consider delaying trastuzumab emtansine treatment until the antiretroviral drug is cleared from the circulation (approximately 4 elimination half-lives), if possible. If trastuzumab emtansine cannot be delayed, monitor closely for toxicity.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero no se recomienda. Trastuzumab emtansina es un conjugado de anticuerpo monoclonal-fármaco. Trastuzumab no experimenta metabolismo mediado por CYP. Sin embargo, DM1 (un componente activo de la emtansina) se metaboliza por el CYP3A4. No se recomienda la administración conjunta debido a la posibilidad de un aumento en la exposición a DM1 y la toxicidad. Considere cambiar a un régimen antirretroviral sin efectos inhibitorios sobre el CYP3A4. En caso que la administración conjunta sea inevitable, considere la posibilidad de retrasar el tratamiento con trastuzumab emtansina hasta que el fármaco antirretroviral se elimine de la circulación (aproximadamente 4 vidas medias de eliminación). Si trastuzumab emtansina no se puede retrasar, monitoree de cerca la toxicidad.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores no nucleósidos de la transcriptasa reversa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Trastuzumab emtansine is a monoclonal antibody-drug conjugate. Trastuzumab does not undergo CYP mediated metabolism, whereas DM1 (an active component of emtansine) is metabolized by CYP3A4. Although efavirenz is a moderate inducer of CYP3A4, no clinically relevant interaction is expected with trastuzumab emtansine.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. Trastuzumab emtansina es un conjugado de anticuerpo monoclonal-fármaco. Trastuzumab no experimenta metabolismo mediado por CYP, mientras que el DM1 (un componente activo de la emtansina) se metaboliza por el CYP3A4. Si bien el efavirenz es un inductor moderado del CYP3A4, no se espera interacción clínicamente relevante con trastuzumab emtansina.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Filgrastim is eliminated mainly by neutrophil-mediated clearance and renal excretion. Albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids. In vitro human microsomal studies and limited in vivo drug-drug interaction data indicate that albuvirtide has no inhibiting or inducing properties on P450 enzymes.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. Filgrastim se elimina principalmente por clearance mediado por neutrófilos y excreción renal. La albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes. Los estudios microsómicos humanos in vitro y los datos limitados de interacción farmacológica in vivo indican que la albuvirtida no tiene propiedades inhibidoras o inductoras en las enzimas P450.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Filgrastim is eliminated mainly by neutrophil-mediated clearance and renal excretion whereas ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. Filgrastim se elimina principalmente por clearance mediado por neutrófilos y excreción renal, mientras que es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Ascorbic acid is oxidised to dehydroascorbic acid where some is metabolised to oxalic acid and the inactive ascorbate-2-sulphate. Large doses are rapidly excreted in the urine when in excess of the requirements of the body. Atazanavir does not interfere with this metabolic pathway.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El ácido ascórbico se oxida a ácido deshidroascórbico, donde parte se metaboliza a ácido oxálico y al ascorbato-2-sulfato inactivo. En la orina se excretan rápidamente grandes dosis cuando exceden los requisitos del cuerpo. El atazanavir no interfiere con esta vía metabólica.

Interaction_Status: Potential interaction likely to be of weak intensity. Additional action/monitoring or dosage adjustment is unlikely to be required.
Interaction_Status_ES: La interacción potencial probablemente sea de baja intensidad. Es poco probable que se requiera acción/monitoreo adicional o ajuste de dosis.
Description:
Coadministration of indinavir (800 mg every 8 hours, four doses) and vitamin C (1000 mg/day for 7 days) was studied in 7 HIV-negative subjects. All subjects were given a vitamin C content-controlled diet for 1 week before the study began and throughout the study period. Indinavir Cmax, AUC and Cmin decreased by 20%, 14% and 32%, respectively, in the presence of vitamin C. The clinical significance of these findings remains to be established.
Effect of high-dose vitamin C on the steady-state pharmacokinetics of the protease inhibitor indinavir in healthy volunteers. Slain D, Amsden JR, Khakoo RA, et al. Pharmacother, 2005, 25(2): 165-70.
Summary: Coadministration with indinavir/ritonavir has not been studied. Coadministration of high doses of ascorbic acid (1000 mg daily) and indinavir alone (800 mg every 8 hours) decreased steady state indinavir Cmax and AUC by 20%, 14% and 32%, respectively (n=7). The mechanism of this interaction and clinical significance are unknown.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta con indinavir/ritonavir La administración conjunta de altas dosis de ácido ascórbico (1000 mg al día) e indinavir (800 mg cada 8 horas) redujo significativamente la Cmáx y el AUC de indinavir en estado estacionario en un 20% y 14%, respectivamente (n=7). Se desconoce el mecanismo y la importancia clínica de esta interacción.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Ascorbic acid is oxidised to dehydroascorbic acid where some is metabolised to oxalic acid and the inactive ascorbate-2-sulphate. Large doses are rapidly excreted in the urine when in excess of the requirements of the body. There is therefore little potential for an interaction with doravirine via modulation of, or competition for metabolic pathways.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El ácido ascórbico se oxida a ácido deshidroascórbico, donde parte se metaboliza a ácido oxálico y al ascorbato-2-sulfato inactivo. En la orina se excretan rápidamente grandes dosis cuando exceden los requisitos del cuerpo. Por lo tanto, existe poco potencial para la interacción con doravirina mediante la modulación o la competencia por las vías metabólicas.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores no nucleósidos de la transcriptasa reversa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. Ascorbic acid is oxidised to dehydroascorbic acid where some is metabolised to oxalic acid and the inactive ascorbate-2-sulphate. Large doses of ascorbic acid may cause the urine to become acidic causing unexpected renal tubular reabsorption of acidic drugs, thus producing an exaggerated response. Conversely basic drugs may exhibit decreased reabsorption resulting in a decreased therapeutic effect. No significant interactions are expected with doravirine or lamivudine. Tenofovir-DF is predominantly eliminated unchanged via active renal tubular secretion, but unless treatment with ascorbic acid involves large doses of prolonged duration, significant interactions are not expected.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. El ácido ascórbico se oxida a ácido deshidroascórbico, donde parte se metaboliza a ácido oxálico y al ascorbato-2-sulfato inactivo. Grandes dosis de ácido ascórbico pueden causar que la orina se torne ácida, lo cual produce una inesperada reabsorción tubular renal de fármacos ácidos y, consecuentemente, causa una respuesta exagerada. Por el contrario, los fármacos básicos pueden exhibir una reabsorción disminuida, lo que produce un efecto terapéutico disminuido. No se esperan interacciones significativas con doravirina o lamivudina. El tenofovir-DF se elimina predominantemente sin cambios a través de la secreción tubular renal activa, pero a menos que el tratamiento con ácido ascórbico implique grandes dosis de duración prolongada, no se esperan interacciones significativas.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Description:
Concentrations of 25-hydroxy vitamin D were measured in 88 HIV+ subjects who received vitamin D3 supplements. Although use of efavirenz was associated with lower baseline hydroxy vitamin D concentrations, efavirenz did not diminish the response to vitamin D supplementation.
Serum 25-hydroxyvitamin D response to vitamin D3 supplementation 50,000 IU monthly in youth with HIV-1 infection. Havens PL, Mulligan K, Hazra R, et al.J Clin Endocrinol Metab, 2012, 97(11): 4004-13.

Pharmacokinetic modelling of vitamin D3 supplementation from 422 HIV-infected patients showed no significant differences in concentrations of 25-hydroxycolecalciferol related to antiretroviral drugs.
Vitamin D3 supplementation scheme in HIV-infected patients based upon pharmacokinetic modelling of 25-hydroxycholecalciferol. Foissac, F, Treluyer JM, Souberbielle JC, et al. Br J Clin Pharmacol, 2013, 75(5): 1312-1320.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. Metabolism of vitamin D to active metabolites occurs in the liver and kidneys, and is thought to involve CYP3A4 and CYP24A1. In vitro studies have shown rifampicin (an enzyme inducer) increased metabolism of vitamin D and introduction of 6',7'-dihydroxybergamottin (a CYP3A4 inhibitor in grapefruit juice) reversed the effects of rifampicin on vitamin D clearance. These studies suggest that inducers of CYP3A4 (such as efavirenz) may increase metabolism of vitamin D and therefore reduce its effect. Various observational studies have reported increased risk for vitamin D deficiency in patients taking efavirenz containing regimens. However, no effect of efavirenz on the response to vitamin D supplementation was observed in a clinical study nor found in a PK modelling study.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. El metabolismo de la vitamina D a metabolitos activos ocurre por vía hepática y renal, y se cree que involucra al CYP3A4 y al CYP24A1. Los estudios in vitro han demostrado que la rifampicina (un inductor enzimático) aumentó el metabolismo de la vitamina D y la introducción de 6',7'-dihidroxibergamotina (un inhibidor del CYP3A4 que se encuentra en el jugo de pomelo o toronja) revirtió los efectos de la rifampicina en el clearance de vitamina D. Estos estudios sugieren que los inductores del CYP3A4 (como efavirenz) pueden aumentar el metabolismo de la vitamina D y, por lo tanto, reducir su efecto. Varios estudios observacionales reportaron un mayor riesgo de deficiencia de vitamina D en pacientes que toman regímenes que contienen efavirenz. Sin embargo, no se encontró ningún efecto de efavirenz en la respuesta a la suplementación con vitamina D en un estudio de modelado PK.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Description:
Pharmacokinetic modelling of vitamin D3 supplementation from 422 HIV-infected patients showed no significant differences in concentrations of 25-hydroxycolecalciferol related to antiretroviral drugs.
Vitamin D3 supplementation scheme in HIV-infected patients based upon pharmacokinetic modelling of 25-hydroxycholecalciferol. Foissac, F, Treluyer JM, Souberbielle JC, et al. Br J Clin Pharmacol, 2013, 75(5): 1312-1320.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. Metabolism of vitamin D to active metabolites occurs in the liver and kidneys, and is thought to involve CYP3A4 and CYP24A1. In vitro studies have shown rifampicin (an enzyme inducer) increased metabolism of vitamin D and introduction of 6',7'-dihydroxybergamottin (a CYP3A4 inhibitor in grapefruit juice) reversed the effects of rifampicin on vitamin D clearance. Inhibition of CYP3A by elvitegravir/cobicistat is not expected to reduce the effect of vitamin D, but the consequence of CYP3A inhibition on the clinical effect of vitamin D is not known. However, no effect of antiretroviral therapy on the response to vitamin D supplementation was found in a PK modelling study. Significant interactions are not expected with emtricitabine and tenofovir-DF.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. El metabolismo de la vitamina D a metabolitos activos ocurre por vía hepática y renal, y se cree que involucra al CYP3A4 y al CYP24A1. Los estudios in vitro han demostrado que la rifampicina (un inductor enzimático) aumentó el metabolismo de la vitamina D y la introducción de 6',7'-dihidroxibergamotina (un inhibidor del CYP3A4 que se encuentra en el jugo de pomelo o toronja) revirtió los efectos de la rifampicina en el clearance de vitamina D. No se espera que la inhibición del CYP3A por elvitegravir/cobicistat reduzca el efecto de la vitamina D, pero se desconoce la consecuencia de la inhibición del CYP3A sobre el efecto clínico de la vitamina D. Sin embargo, no se encontró ningún efecto de la terapia antirretroviral en la respuesta a la suplementación con vitamina D en un estudio de modelado PK. No se esperan interacciones significativas con emtricitabina y tenofovir-DF.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Metabolism of vitamin D to active metabolites occurs in the liver and kidneys, and is thought to involve CYP3A4 and CYP24A1. There is little potential for an interaction with raltegravir via modulation of, or competition for, metabolic pathways.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El metabolismo de la vitamina D a metabolitos activos ocurre por vía hepática y renal, y se cree que involucra al CYP3A4 y al CYP24A1. Por lo tanto, existe poco potencial para la interacción con raltegravir mediante la modulación o la competencia por las vías metabólicas.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Cyanocobalamin undergoes enterohepatic recycling and is excreted almost entirely in the urine. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. La cianocobalamina experimenta un reciclaje enterohepático y se excreta casi por completo en la orina. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Iodine is converted to iodide, which is trapped in the thyroid gland. Iodides are excreted mainly in the urine with smaller amounts excreted in the faeces, sweat and saliva.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El yodo se convierte en yoduro, que queda atrapado en la glándula tiroides. Los yoduros se excretan principalmente en la orina con cantidades más pequeñas excretadas en las heces, el sudor y la saliva.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Iodine is converted to iodide, which is trapped in the thyroid gland. Iodides are excreted mainly in the urine with smaller amounts excreted in the faeces, sweat and saliva. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones farmacológicas. El yodo se convierte en yoduro, que queda atrapado en la glándula tiroides. Los yoduros se excretan principalmente en la orina con cantidades más pequeñas excretadas en las heces, el sudor y la saliva. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.

Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. Una interacción es poco probable ya que la albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones farmacológicas. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
Biktarvy should not be co-administered simultaneously with iron supplements under fasted conditions. Biktarvy should be administered at least 2 hours before iron supplements, or taken together with food. Simultaneous administration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg single dose) and bictegravir decreased bictegravir AUC and Cmax by 63% and 71% under fasting conditions, but had no significant effect on AUC and decreased Cmax by 25% when given with food.
Biktarvy Summary of Product Characteristics, Gilead Sciences Ltd, June 2019.

Coadministration may decrease bictegravir concentrations. Biktarvy and supplements containing iron can be taken together with food. Routine administration of Biktarvy under fasting conditions together with, or 2 hours after, supplements containing iron is not recommended. Simultaneous coadministration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg single dose) and bictegravir (50 mg single dose) under fasting conditions decreased bictegravir Cmax and AUC by 71% and 63%. Simultaneous coadministration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg single dose) and bictegravir (50 mg single dose) with food decreased bictegravir Cmax and AUC by 25% and 16% when compared to bictegravir alone under fasting conditions.
Biktarvy Prescribing Information, Gilead Sciences Inc, August 2019.

Bictegravir/emtricitabine/tenofovir alafenamide (50/200/25 mg single dose) was administered to HIV-uninfected subjects (n=14) simultaneously, under fasted or fed conditions, with/without ferrous fumarate (324 mg single dose). Simultaneous administration decreased bictegravir AUC by 63% in fasting conditions and by 16% in fed conditions.
Pharmacokinetics (PK) of bictegravir (BIC) in combination with polyvalent cation containing (PVCC) antacids and supplements. Mathias A, Lutz J, West S, et al. J Int Aids Soc, 2018, 21 (S8): 167-168 (abstract P260).
Summary: As with other HIV integrase inhibitors, bictegravir may be subject to chelation by high concentrations of divalent cations which may result in reduced bictegravir concentrations. The simultaneous administration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) and bictegravir with food did not significantly impair bictegravir exposure whereas exposure was decreased by 63% during simultaneous administration in fasted conditions. It is recommended to administer bictegravir and ferrous fumarate simultaneously with food.
Summary_ES: Al igual que con otros inhibidores de la integrasa del VIH, el bictegravir puede estar sujeto a quelación por altas concentraciones de cationes divalentes que pueden dar como resultado concentraciones reducidas de bictegravir. La administración simultánea de fumarato ferroso (324 mg) y bictegravir con alimentos no afectó significativamente la exposición a bictegravir, mientras que la exposición disminuyó en un 63% durante la administración simultánea en ayunas. Se recomienda administrar bictegravir y fumarato ferroso simultáneamente con los alimentos.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
Coadministration with iron supplements decreased dolutegravir AUC, Cmax and Cmin by 54%, 57% and 56%, respectively. Iron supplements should be taken well separated in time from the administration of dolutegravir (minimum 2 hours after or 6 hours before). Factors that decrease dolutegravir exposure should be avoided in the presence of integrase class resistance. This includes co-administration with medicinal products that reduce dolutegravir exposure (e.g. iron supplements).
Tivicay Summary of Product Characteristics, ViiV Healthcare, March 2019.

Coadministration may decrease dolutegravir concentrations. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) and dolutegravir (50 mg single dose) was studied under fasted, fed and temporally separated conditions. Simultaneous coadministration to fasting subjects (n=11) decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Cmin by 57%, 54% and 56%, respectively. Simultaneous coadministration to fed subjects (n=11) increased dolutegravir Cmax by 3%, decreased AUC by 2%, and had no effect on Cmin. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate 2 h after dolutegravir (n=10) decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Cmin by 1%, 5% and 8%, respectively. Administer dolutegravir 2 hours before or 6 hours after taking supplements containing iron. Alternatively, dolutegravir and supplements containing calcium can be taken together with food.
Tivicay US Prescribing Information, ViiV Healthcare, July 2019.
Summary: Administration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) simultaneously under fed conditions or 2 hours after dolutegravir had no significant effect on dolutegravir exposure. However, when coadministered simultaneously in the fasted state, dolutegravir AUC and Cmax decreased by 54% and 57%, respectively. Administer dolutegravir 2 hours before or 6 hours after ferrous fumarate. The US Prescribing information suggests that, alternatively, dolutegravir and supplements containing iron can be taken together with food. Medicinal products that reduce dolutegravir exposure (e.g. ferrous fumarate) should be avoided in the presence of integrase class resistance.
Summary_ES: La administración de fumarato ferroso (324 mg) simultáneamente en condiciones de alimentación o 2 horas después de dolutegravir no tuvo un efecto significativo sobre la exposición a dolutegravir. Sin embargo, cuando se coadministra simultáneamente en ayunas, el AUC y la Cmáx de dolutegravir disminuyeron un 54% y un 57%, respectivamente. Administre dolutegravir 2 horas antes o 6 horas después del fumarato ferroso. La información prescriptiva de EEUU sugiere que, alternativamente, el dolutegravir y los suplementos que contienen hierro pueden tomarse junto con los alimentos. Deben evitarse los medicamentos que reducen la exposición a dolutegravir (por ejemplo, fumarato ferroso) en presencia de resistencia a la clase integrasa.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
Coadministration of iron supplements (fasted intake) decreased dolutegravir AUC, Cmax and C24 by 54%, 57% and 56%, respectively, due to complex binding to polyvalent ions. The stated reductions in dolutegravir exposure were observed with the intake of dolutegravir during fasted conditions. In fed state, the changes in exposure following intake together with iron supplements were modified by the food effect, resulting in an exposure similar to that obtained with dolutegravir administered in the fasted state. When taken with food, Dovato and supplements or multivitamins containing iron can be taken at the same time. If Dovato is taken in a fasted state, such supplements should be taken a minimum 2 hours after or 6 hours before the intake of Dovato.
Dovato Summary of Product Characteristics, ViiV Healthcare, July 2019.

Coadministration may decrease dolutegravir concentrations. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) and dolutegravir (50 mg single dose) was studied under fasted, fed and temporally separated conditions. Simultaneous coadministration to fasting subjects decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Cmin by 57%, 54% and56%, respectively. Simultaneous coadministration to fed subjects increased dolutegravir Cmax by 3%, decreased AUC by 2%, and had no effect on Cmin. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate 2 h after dolutegravir decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Cmin by 1%, 5% and 8%, respectively. When taken with food, Dovato and supplements containing iron can be taken at the same time. Under fasting conditions, Dovato should be taken 2 hours before or 6 hours after taking supplements containing iron.
Dovato US Prescribing Information, ViiV Healthcare, April 2019.
Summary: Coadministration with Dovato (dolutegravir/lamivudine) has not been studied. No interaction is expected with lamivudine. Administration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) simultaneously under fed conditions or 2 hours after dolutegravir had no significant effect on dolutegravir exposure. However, when coadministered simultaneously in the fasted state, dolutegravir AUC and Cmax decreased by 54% and 57%, respectively. When taken with food, Dovato and ferrous fumarate can be taken at the same time. Under fasting conditions, Dovato should be taken 2 hours before or 6 hours after taking ferrous fumarate.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta con Dovato (dolutegravir/lamivudina). No se espera interacción con lamivudina. La administración de fumarato ferroso (324 mg) simultáneamente en condiciones de alimentación o 2 horas después de dolutegravir no tuvo un efecto significativo sobre la exposición a dolutegravir. Sin embargo, cuando se coadministra simultáneamente en ayunas, el AUC y la Cmáx de dolutegravir disminuyeron un 54% y un 57%, respectivamente. Cuando se toma con alimentos, Dovato y fumarato ferroso se pueden tomar al mismo tiempo. En condiciones de ayuno, Dovato debe tomarse 2 horas antes o 6 horas después de tomar fumarato ferroso.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
Iron supplements should be taken well separated in time from the administration of Triumeq. Triumeq is recommended to be administered 2 hours before or 6 hours after taking iron supplements. Coadministration of iron supplements and dolutegravir decreased dolutegravir AUC, Cmax and C24 by 54%, 57% and 56%, respectively, due to complex binding to polyvalent ions.
Triumeq Summary of Product Characteristics, ViiV Healthcare, June 2019.

Coadministration may decrease dolutegravir concentrations. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) and dolutegravir (50 mg single dose) was studied under fasted, fed and temporally separated conditions. Simultaneous coadministration to fasting subjects (n=11) decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Cmin by 57%, 54% and 56%, respectively. Simultaneous coadministration to fed subjects (n=11) increased dolutegravir Cmax by 3%, decreased AUC by 2%, and had no effect on Cmin. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate 2 h after dolutegravir (n=10) decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Cmin by 1%, 5% and 8%, respectively. Administer Triumeq 2 hours before or 6 hours after taking supplements containing iron. Alternatively, Triumeq and supplements containing iron can be taken together with food.
Triumeq US Prescribing Information, ViiV Healthcare, May 2019.
Summary: Coadministration with Triumeq (dolutegravir/abacavir/lamivudine) has not been studied. No interaction is expected with abacavir or lamivudine. Administration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) simultaneously under fed conditions or 2 hours after dolutegravir had no significant effect on dolutegravir exposure. However, when coadministered simultaneously in the fasted state, dolutegravir AUC and Cmax decreased by 54% and 57%, respectively. Administer Triumeq 2 hours before or 6 hours after taking ferrous fumarate. The US product information for Triumeq suggests that, alternatively, Triumeq and supplements containing iron can be taken together with food.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta con Triumeq (dolutegravir/abacavir/lamivudina). No se espera interacción con abacavir o lamivudina. La administración de fumarato ferroso (324 mg) simultáneamente en condiciones de alimentación o 2 horas después de dolutegravir no tuvo un efecto significativo sobre la exposición a dolutegravir. Sin embargo, cuando se coadministra simultáneamente en ayunas, el AUC y la Cmáx de dolutegravir disminuyeron un 54% y un 57%, respectivamente. Administre Triumeq 2 horas antes o 6 horas después del fumarato ferroso. La información prescriptiva de EEUU sugiere que, alternativamente, Triumeq y los suplementos que contienen hierro pueden tomarse junto con los alimentos.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
The combination of Juluca and supplements should be used with particular caution. Iron supplements should be co-administered at the same time as Juluca, with a meal. If iron supplements cannot be taken at the same time as Juluca, these supplements should be taken well separated in time from the administration of Juluca (minimum 6 hours before or 4 hours after). Coadministration of iron supplements and dolutegravir decreased dolutegravir AUC, Cmax and C24 by 54%, 57% and 56%, respectively (complex binding to polyvalent ions).
Juluca Summary of Product Characteristics, ViiV Healthcare Ltd, May 2018.


Coadministration is expected to decrease dolutegravir concentrations. Administer Juluca and supplements containing iron together with a meal or take Juluca 4 hours before or 6 hours after taking these supplements. Coadministration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) and dolutegravir (50 mg single dose) was studied when given simultaneously in fasted and fed conditions, and 2 h after dolutegravir. Simultaneous administration decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Ctrough by 57%, 54% and 56%, respectively, in fasted conditions (n=11). In fed conditions, simultaneous administration increased dolutegravir Cmax by 3%, decreased AUC by 2% and had no effect on Ctrough (n=11). Administration 2 h after dolutegravir decreased dolutegravir Cmax, AUC and Ctrough by 1%, 5% and 8%, respectively (n=10).
Juluca US Prescribing Information, ViiV Healthcare Ltd, September 2018.
Summary: Coadministration of dolutegravir/rilpivirine has not been studied. No interaction is expected with rilpivirine. Administration of ferrous fumarate (324 mg) simultaneously under fed conditions or 2 hours after dolutegravir (50 mg single dose) had no significant effect on dolutegravir exposure. However, when coadministered simultaneously in the fasted state, dolutegravir AUC, Cmax and Ctrough decreased by 54%, 57% and 56%, respectively. The combination of dolutegravir/rilpivirine and ferrous fumarate should be used with particular caution. Ferrous fumarate should be co-administered at the same time as dolutegravir/rilpivirine with a meal. If ferrous fumarate cannot be taken at the same time as dolutegravir/rilpivirine, it should be taken well separated in time from the administration of dolutegravir/rilpivirine (minimum 6 hours before or 4 hours after).
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta con dolutegravir/rilpivirina. No se espera interacción con rilpivirina. La administración de fumarato ferroso (324 mg) simultáneamente en condiciones de alimentación o 2 horas después del dolutegravir (50 mg, dosis única) no tuvo un efecto significativo sobre la exposición al dolutegravir. Sin embargo, cuando se coadministra simultáneamente en ayunas, el AUC, la Cmáx y la Cmin de dolutegravir disminuyeron 54%, 57% y 56%, respectivamente. La combinación de dolutegravir/rilpivirina y fumarato ferroso debe usarse con especial precaución. El fumarato ferroso debe administrarse conjuntamente al mismo tiempo que dolutegravir/rilpivirina con una comida. Si el fumarato ferroso no puede tomarse al mismo tiempo que dolutegravir/rilpivirina, debe tomarse bien espaciado en tiempo a partir de la administración de dolutegravir/rilpivirina (mínimo 6 horas antes o 4 horas después).

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
Interaction not studied with any of the components of Genvoya. As the effect of cationic complexation of elvitegravir cannot be excluded when Genvoya is co-administered with multivitamin supplements, it is recommended to separate Genvoya and multivitamin supplements dosing by at least 4 hours.
Genvoya Summary of Product Characteristics, Gilead Sciences International Ltd, November 2015.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. As with other HIV integrase inhibitors, elvitegravir may be subject to chelation by high concentrations of divalent cations which may result in reduced elvitegravir concentrations. Separating the administration of integrase inhibitors and ferrous fumarate by at least 4 hours is recommended. Significant interactions are not expected with cobicistat, emtricitabine and tenofovir alafenamide.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. Al igual que con otros inhibidores de la integrasa del VIH, el elvitegravir puede estar sujeto a quelación por altas concentraciones de cationes divalentes que pueden dar como resultado concentraciones reducidas de elvitegravir. Se recomienda separar la administración de inhibidores de la integrasa y fumarato ferroso en al menos 4 horas. No se esperan interacciones significativas con cobicistat, emtricitabina y tenofovir alafenamida.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
In vitro studies have shown raltegravir cellular permeativity was decreased in the presence of the divalent cations magnesium and calcium, but not in the presence of the monovalent cation potassium. Raltegravir may bind to the divalent metals and form a metal-drug complex which is unable to cross the cell membrane.
Divalent metals and pH alter raltegravir disposition in Vitro. Moss DM, Siccardi M, Murphy M, at al. Antimicrob Agents Chemother, 2012, 56(6): 3020-6.
Summary: Caution is recommended when prescribing ferrous fumarate. Raltegravir binds to divalent cations such as iron and forms a complex at the level of the gastro-intestinal tract which results in less raltegravir being absorbed. Administration of raltegravir 400 mg twice daily should be separated by at least 4 hours. Importantly, drug-drug interaction studies with antacids containing divalent cations have shown a more pronounced reduction in raltegravir Cmin when raltegravir was administered once daily compared to a twice daily regimen. A similar effect for ferrous fumarate cannot be excluded, therefore, twice daily administration of raltegravir should be preferred.
Summary_ES: Se recomienda precaución al prescribir fumarato ferroso. El raltegravir se une a los cationes divalentes como el hierro y forma un complejo a nivel del tracto gastrointestinal, lo cual produce que se absorba menos raltegravir. La administración de raltegravir 400 mg dos veces al día debe estar espaciada por al menos 4 horas. Es importante destacar que los estudios de interacción farmacológica con antiácidos que contienen cationes divalentes han mostrado una reducción más pronunciada en la Cmin de raltegravir cuando se administró raltegravir una vez al día en comparación con un régimen de dos veces al día. No se puede excluir un efecto similar para el fumarato ferroso, por lo cual se debe preferir la administración de raltegravir dos veces al día.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Cyanocobalamin undergoes enterohepatic recycling and is excreted almost entirely in the urine.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La cianocobalamina experimenta un reciclaje enterohepático y se excreta casi por completo en la orina.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Nicotinamide is metabolized by nicotinamide methyltransferase to N-methylnicotinamide which is then metabolized by xanthine oxidase and aldehyde oxidase. Renal elimination of unchanged nicotinamide is minimal.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La nicotinamida se convierte en N-metilnicotinamida por la nicotinamida metiltransferasa, que a su vez se metaboliza por la xantina oxidasa y la aldehído oxidasa. La eliminación renal de nicotinamida inalterada es mínima.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Nicotinamide is metabolized by nicotinamide methyltransferase to N-methylnicotinamide which is then metabolized by xanthine oxidase and aldehyde oxidase. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. La nicotinamida se convierte en N-metilnicotinamida por la nicotinamida metiltransferasa, que a su vez se metaboliza por la xantina oxidasa y la aldehído oxidasa. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Pyridoxine is absorbed from the GI tract and is converted to the active form pyridoxal phosphate. It is excreted in the urine as 4-pyridoxic acid. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. La piridoxina se absorbe del tracto gastrointestinal y se convierte en la forma activa fosfato de piridoxal. Se excreta en la orina como ácido 4-piridóxico. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Description: A clinical study evaluated retinol levels in patients with or without HAART and assessed the effect of antiretroviral agents on retinal dehydrogenase (RALDH), a key enzyme involved in retinoic acid synthesis. Plasma retinol levels, measured in six patients receiving HAART and in five others with no antiretroviral therapy, were correlated with levels of serum retinol-binding proteins. Plasma retinol levels in patients receiving HAART were decreased in comparison with those not receiving antiretroviral drugs (51 +/- 5 versus 66 +/- 11 microg/dl; P = 0.03), whereas retinol-binding protein levels were increased (68 +/- 18 versus 45 +/- 10 mg/l; P = 0.04). RALDH activity was heightened by ritonavir (24%), indinavir (17%), saquinavir (17%), zalcitabine (14%), delavirdine (12%) and nelfinavir (10%) and decreased (22%) by DMP-450. RALDH gene expression was induced only by indinavir. These data indicate that certain retinoid-like adverse effects in HAART-receiving patients are not due to higher retinol levels. Enhanced RALDH activity or/and gene expression by some protease inhibitors could increase retinoic acid concentrations. Elevated retinoic acid levels might be responsible for retinoid-like or other adverse effects due to alterations in the expression of retinoic acid-responsive genes.Toma E, Devost D, Chow Lan N, Bhat PV. HIV-protease inhibitors alter retinoic acid synthesis. AIDS. 2001 Oct 19;15(15):1979-84.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. A clinical study demonstrated that ritonavir, indinavir, nelfinavir and saquinavir increased the activity of retinal dehydrogenase, an enzyme involved in retinoic acid synthesis. Enhanced retinal dehydrogenase activity by some protease inhibitors could increase retinoic acid concentrations. This is unlikely to be of clinical importance, unless high doses of retinol supplementation are given long term.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. Un estudio clínico demostró que ritonavir, indinavir, nelfinavir y saquinavir aumentaron la actividad de la deshidrogenasa retiniana, una enzima involucrada en la síntesis del ácido retinoico. La actividad deshidrogenasa retiniana ampliada por algunos inhibidores de la proteasa podría aumentar las concentraciones de ácido retinoico. Es poco probable que esto tenga importancia clínica, a menos que se administren altas dosis de suplementos de retinol a largo plazo.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores no nucleósidos de la transcriptasa reversa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Vitamin A esters are hydrolysed by pancreatic enzymes to retinol, which is then absorbed and re-esterified. Some retinol is stored in the liver. Retinol not stored in the liver undergoes glucuronide conjugation and subsequent oxidation to retinal and retinoic acid.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. Los ésteres de vitamina A se hidrolizan por enzimas pancreáticas a retinol, que luego se absorbe y reesterifica. Parte del retinol se almacena en el hígado. El retinol no almacenado en el hígado experimenta conjugación de glucurónido y posterior oxidación a ácido retinal y retinoico.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied, but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Vitamin A esters are hydrolysed by pancreatic enzymes to retinol, which is then absorbed and re-esterified. Some retinol is stored in the liver. Retinol not stored in the liver undergoes glucuronide conjugation and subsequent oxidation to retinal and retinoic acid. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. Los ésteres de vitamina A se hidrolizan por enzimas pancreáticas a retinol, que luego se absorbe y reesterifica. Parte del retinol se almacena en el hígado. El retinol no almacenado en el hígado experimenta conjugación de glucurónido y posterior oxidación a ácido retinal y retinoico. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones farmacológicas. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. La albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes.

Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Description:
Tipranavir capsules, co-administered with low dose ritonavir, should be used with caution in patients who are receiving medicinal products known to increase the risk of bleeding such as antiplatelet agents and anticoagulants or who are taking supplemental vitamin E. Based on the limits of exposure available from observation in clinical trials, it is recommended not to co-administer to patients more than 1,200 IU vitamin E per day.
Aptivus (soft capsules) Summary of Product Characteristics, Boehringer Ingelheim Ltd, August 2018.

Tipranavir oral solution, co-administered with low dose ritonavir, should be used with caution in patients are receiving medicinal products known to increase the risk of bleeding such as antiplatelet agents and anticoagulants or who are taking supplemental vitamin E. Patients taking tipranavir oral solution should be advised not to take any supplemental vitamin E.
Aptivus (oral solution) Summary of Product Characteristics, Boehringer Ingelheim Ltd, August 2018.

Tipranavir/ritonavir should be used with caution in patients who are receiving medications known to increase the risk of bleeding such as antiplatelet agents and anticoagulants, or who are taking supplemental high doses of vitamin E. Patients taking tipranavir oral solution should be advised not to take supplemental vitamin E greater than a standard multivitamin as tipranavir oral solution contains 116 IU/mL of vitamin E which is higher than the Reference Daily Intake (adults 30 IU, pediatrics approximately 10 IU).
Aptivus US Prescribing Information, Boehringer Ingelheim Pharmaceuticals Inc, November 2019.
Summary: Tipranavir/ritonavir should be used with caution in patients who taking supplemental vitamin E as these patients may be at risk of increased bleeding. Tipranavir oral solution has a higher vitamin E content than tipranavir capsules. The European product labels advise not to coadminister more than 1200 IU of vitamin E per day with tipranavir capsules and that patients taking tipranavir oral solution should not take any supplemental vitamin E. The US product label for tipranavir advises not to take tipranavir oral solution with supplemental vitamin E greater than a standard multivitamin as tipranavir oral solution contains 116 IU/mL of vitamin E which is higher than the Reference Daily Intake.
Summary_ES: Tipranavir/ritonavir debe utilizarse con precaución en pacientes que toman dosis suplementarias de vitamina E, ya que estos pacientes pueden estar en riesgo de un aumento hemorrágico. La solución oral de tipranavir tiene un mayor contenido de vitamina E que las cápsulas de tipranavir. Las etiquetas de los productos europeos aconsejan no coadministrar más de 1200 UI de vitamina E por día con cápsulas de tipranavir y que los pacientes que toman la solución oral de tipranavir no deben tomar ninguna vitamina E suplementaria. La etiqueta del producto de EEUU para tipranavir aconseja no tomar la solución oral de tipranavir con vitamina E suplementaria superior a una multivitamina estándar dado que la solución oral de tipranavir contiene 116 UI/ml de vitamina E, que es más alta que la ingesta diaria de referencia.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones farmacológicas. Es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

Interaction_Status: These drugs should not be coadministered
Interaction_Status_ES: Estos fármacos no deben administrarse en conjunto.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied and is not recommended. Eletriptan is metabolised by CYP3A4 and concentrations may increase due to inhibition of CYP3A4 by atazanavir. Coadministration with ketoconazole (a strong CYP3A4 inhibitor) increased eletriptan Cmax and AUC by 2.7 and 5.9 fold, respectively. The US product label for eletriptan contraindicates its use with potent CYP3A4 inhibitors whereas the European product label advises that it should not be used with potent CYP3A4 inhibitors.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta y no se recomienda. El eletriptán se metaboliza por el CYP3A4 y las concentraciones pueden aumentar debido a la inhibición del CYP3A4 por atazanavir. La administración conjunta con ketoconazol (un inhibidor potente del CYP3A4) aumentó la Cmáx y el AUC de eletriptán en 2,7 y 5,9 veces, respectivamente. La etiqueta del producto estadounidense para el eletriptán contraindica su uso con inhibidores potentes del CYP3A4, mientras que la etiqueta europea del producto informa que no debe usarse con inhibidores potentes del CYP3A4.

Summary: Coadministration has not been studied and is not recommended. Eletriptan is metabolised by CYP3A4 and concentrations may increase due to inhibition of CYP3A4 by darunavir/cobicstat. Coadministration with ketoconazole (a strong CYP3A4 inhibitor) increased eletriptan Cmax and AUC by 2.7 and 5.9 fold, respectively. The US product label for eletriptan contraindicates its use with potent CYP3A4 inhibitors whereas the European product label advises that it should not be used with potent CYP3A4 inhibitors. No interaction is expected with emtricitabine and tenofovir alafenamide.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta y no se recomienda. El eletriptán se metaboliza por el CYP3A4 y las concentraciones pueden aumentar debido a la inhibición del CYP3A4 por darunavir/cobicistat. La administración conjunta con ketoconazol (un inhibidor potente del CYP3A4) aumentó la Cmáx y el AUC de eletriptán en 2,7 y 5,9 veces, respectivamente. La etiqueta del producto estadounidense para el eletriptán contraindica su uso con inhibidores potentes del CYP3A4, mientras que la etiqueta europea del producto informa que no debe usarse con inhibidores potentes del CYP3A4. No se espera interacción con emtricitabina y tenofovir alafenamida.

Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance, as well as limited drug-drug interaction data, a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. Eletriptan is metabolised by CYP3A4. Albuvirtide is a peptide which is eliminated by catabolism to its constituent amino acids. In vitro human microsomal studies and limited in vivo drug-drug interaction data indicate that albuvirtide has no inhibiting or inducing properties on P450 enzymes.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, así como de los datos limitados sobre interacción farmacológica, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. El eletriptán se metaboliza por el CYP3A4. La albuvirtida es un péptido que se elimina por vía catabólica a sus aminoácidos constituyentes. Los estudios microsómicos humanos in vitro y los datos limitados de interacción farmacológica in vivo indican que la albuvirtida no tiene propiedades inhibidoras o inductoras en las enzimas P450.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status_ES: No se espera interacción clínicamente significativa.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied but based on metabolism and clearance a clinically significant interaction is unlikely. No drug interaction studies have been conducted with ibalizumab: based on ibalizumab’s mechanism of action and target-mediated drug disposition, drug-drug interactions are not expected. Eletriptan is metabolised by CYP3A4 whereas ibalizumab, a monoclonal antibody binding to the CD4 receptor, is likely to be eliminated via intracellular catabolism similarly to other monoclonal antibodies.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta pero, en función del metabolismo y el clearance, es poco probable que ocurra una interacción clínicamente significativa. No se han realizado estudios de interacciones farmacológicas con ibalizumab: de acuerdo con el mecanismo de acción del ibalizumab y la disposición farmacológica mediada por meta, no se esperan interacciones entre fármacos. El eletriptán se metaboliza por el CYP3A4, mientras que es probable que el ibalizumab, un anticuerpo monoclonal que se une al receptor CD4, se elimine mediante catabolismo intracelular de forma similar a otros anticuerpos monoclonales.

drug_class_name_ES: Antirretrovirales (Inhibidores de la entrada e integrasa)
Interaction_Status: Potential interaction that may require close monitoring, alteration of drug dosage or timing of administration
Interaction_Status_ES: Posible interacción que puede requerir monitoreo estrecho, alteración de la dosis del fármaco o del tiempo de administración.
Summary: Coadministration has not been studied. Moxonidine is only minimally metabolized and is eliminated renally by glomerular filtration and active secretion, mainly as unchanged moxonidine. The renal transporter involved in moxonidine excretion is unknown but does not seem to involve P-glycoprotein or renal organic cation (OCT) transporters. No interaction is expected with elvitegravir/cobicistat or with emtricitabine (eliminated by OCT2), however, an interaction with tenofovir-DF cannot be excluded.
Summary_ES: No se ha estudiado la administración conjunta. La moxonidina se metaboliza sólo mínimamente y se elimina por vía renal mediante filtración glomerular y secreción activa, principalmente como moxonidina inalterada. Se desconoce el transportador renal involucrado en la excreción de moxonidina, pero no parece involucrar a los transportadores de cationes orgánicos (OCT) renales o de glicoproteína P. No se espera interacción con elvitegravir/cobicistat o con emtricitabina (eliminada por OCT2), aunque no se puede excluir una interacción con tenofovir-DF.
